name: Wendy's
vicinity: 4250 Nannie Helen Burroughs Avenue Northeast, Washington

reviews.text: This seems to be the only out of date Wendy’s in town, this place needs to be remodeled and up to date. The parking lot is hard to get in/out of, the parking lot holds water, it’s needs new parking spaces striping lines. I forgot to add my picture of my food, but the breakfast was hot and fresh.

The cashier had a great personality, very customer service oriented.  The manager on duty was her sister, and she engaged with customers and her Team so professionally, I'll surely be going back.  I only purchased medium french fries, and my daughter told the truth, they are absolutely freshly made and delicious!
Wonderful staff. I enjoyed talking to the staff at the register. One of the cooks gave a child two free toys I enjoy them. But the area is dark at night and sick individuals come in.
Need to do a better job at the drive through during late night hours… more night shift workers, faster pace. The lines at night are just ridiculously long for “FAST FOOD”

Only Use The Drive Through!

This place is perfectly fine if you don't go in, and don't mind longish lines in the drive thru. The food here is what you'd normally expect from Wendy's. No complaints at all with that. It's the inside that's the problem. It looks like the employees just gave up on cleaning it. Never seen such a poorly kept interior of a chain restaurant.

name: Subway
vicinity: 4800 Nannie Helen Burroughs Avenue Northeast, Washington

reviews.text: This subway is great place to chilling with friends and their sandwiches are so fresh to eat . I saw so many Young person are enjoying inside of this place . Their stuff were so friendly and understanding.

It was clean and the customer service was nice. I don't usually eat subway, but the customer service was so bad and the McDonalds that I came here instead for a six inch. The sandwich was decent and I  would go back again.

New guy was wasting my time asking Double meat. I Want one layer of meat. I usually get the same thing. My son loves Black Forest Ham with lil lettuce and mayo and I get Spicy Italian or the Special of the Day. The Manager was A-Ok. He is Excellent. I use to go there often when I work 2019-2020 DC School year. The manager would fix my sandwiches perfectly. Today this new guy made me repeat my order 5 times before he got it right. Man behind me heard him.
Due to weather ( heavy snow) not crowded. We were the only 2 customers in store. Staff member was very attentive & friendly.
My sandwich was fresh and neatly made and it had just enough tuna on it without me having to ask for more. I was pleasantly surprised.

Green beans were nothing but mush as were the sweet potatoes. and the French fries were old and dry  not cooked on the day of the order.
The chicken breast and catfish were fresh and were the only 2 things we could eat so we paid just under $50 for half a meal from the Shetiff Road location. Will never order from them again.

I was completely surprised when I first came to the location but later left feeling great about the service and food received! Was looking for one near a location and this one came up! The customer service was great and the food was tasty! When they ask if you want seasoning on top, Say yes and get extra! Game Changer!!!

Ordered 16 wings they were good, they pretty much forced fries on me although I didn't want them he said they come with it so I just took them, the fries were small not much to brag about but I liked the wings.

I’m a frequent customer to Hip Hop Fish & Chicken and yes they have made small mistakes with me before but this was a major one that they refuse to take accountability for!!! The cashier charged me double for my order and when I showed the charges to him on my bank statement, he refused to give me a refund!! What led to an argument ended with him finally giving my refund. I recommend going to another location or paying with cash because this was absolutely outrageous.
Sooooo good. Much better than expected. Not greasy nor heavy. Huge portions for the money. Can’t wait to come back for that HipHop Seasoning!

name: McDonald's
vicinity: 4301 Nannie Helen Burroughs Avenue Northeast, Washington

reviews.text:
How did I pay for a fish sandwich meal and two kids meal costing me over $21 and I didn’t even get my fish sandwich just my fries and drink.
And when I called the restaurant no one answers the phone.
Like seriously?
I shouldn’t have to pay for my meal and not receive it.
The person who packed my meal needs to learn to double check before giving someone their meals in the drive thu.
Oh trust and believe I will be there in the AM to speak with a manager.
Unbelievable.

NASTY MANAGER got my child’s order wrong, and insisted that he had to take the nugget happy meal he was already eating from us and put it in the trash in front of my kid before they could do give us a the right meal.   Disgusting and unprofessional location
Its was horrendous wait time. Always! Even when theres no lines. Back in the day, McDonalds mgrs always taught to pick up your feet. Now service to recv service we're on there time. Terrible
I did not get the correct change back from two different orders while ordering T the drive through window. But everything was settled after going inside and speaking to the manager.

They do not have no black people working at that establishment at all nothing but Hispanic people in a black neighborhood and I asked him why they don't have black people working there they said they are lazy and don't come to work and I was very displeased with that so I would never go back to that McDonald's ever again

I ordered a Bacon/Sausage, egg and cheese sandwich, a order of French toast and a lemonade sweet tea. The sandwich was alright and was the only decent thing i got. Unfortunately the French toast was wayyyy to greasy and lacked the typical flavor you’d expect. I understand some stuff is gonna be greasy and I typically don’t mind because it’s justified with the flavor but this was not. The worst part was the drink. I wanted something refreshing as it was already hot outside so i thought some homemade lemonade sweet tea would be perfect but when i took my first gulp I realized too late that the drink definitely was spoiled. A took another small sip to make sure it wasn’t something else but sure enough the drink was definitely bad. I already was a few miles down the road going back to work so i couldn’t get it exchanged so i just threw it out once i got to work. It disappoints me that they don’t taste their stuff or even question the quality of what their serving to people. Also the pricing was a bit high for the area.

I came in after a rainy morning for a quick breakfast. The cashier was friendly, the cook was friendly. Just a nice place to have breakfast. I ordered sodas and the cook brought them out to table. Upon leaving I was even asked, “ How was everything” showed they genuinely cared. I appreciate this!!! Whenever I’m in DC I’ll come back 👊🏿
The nastiest breakfast that ever taste in my life this place should not be able to sell food🤮🤮🤮🤮
Breakfast was hot. Only good thing. Never going back again. Terrible
Real breakfast. Wow.  So much better than places like IHOP.  Down home cooking.

name: Capitol City CDC
vicinity: 4645 Nannie Helen Burroughs Avenue Northeast, Washington

name: AMERICAN BEST WING STOP AND SOULFOOD

reviews.text: Coming soon serving breakfast all day, SOULFOOD, Seafood, BEER&WINE!!

I’m glad they’re in the area the service is professional the food is good and it’s actually fresh and they have a side to the restaurant where you can buy convenience store products we actually need that right here in this particular area.
Food was not good everything taste like it was used before
Yooo!! They are so good!!! I think that was the right location and store. Food fresh! They look clean too!! Who ever cooks the food can really cook!!!

1st time visit. Clean inside... only 2 benches to wait for your order.. it's literally a carryout... no tables/ no option to eat in. Staff is super friendly and responsive. Ordered vegetable fried rice and spring rolls. Food was ready in about 10 min. Hot, fresh and tasty is how I'd sum it up.  I was super surprised and happy to see the chunk vegetables in it!! Lot of Chinese places will just add bean sprouts and scallions or onions to fried rice and call it vegetable fried rice.  This was full of carrots,  broccoli, soybean, onion,  scallion,  and mushroom. The spring rolls were just as good. Cooked perfectly,  great flavor, not overly oily, ans had just the right amount of filling inside. Tasty on their own even without the duck sauce.  I've just found my new favorite Chinese food spot. The hype is real. I'll def be back.
My favorite restaurant in my neighborhood! They even added a complimentary Egg Roll to my order! I recommend the General Tso’s meal.

Bomb Chinese food, it tastes fresh and like they made it with fresh ingredients. I paid about $33 for 6 wings, shrimp fried rice , chicken and broccoli and 2 egg rolls. Best Chinese food on this side hands down.

Best 5 wings w/French Fries
Mumbo Sauce,Hot Sauce,Ketchup & Extra for Barbecue Sauce
Well worth it it was delicious 👍🏾

Been going to this place since 1984. Chicken wings mambo sauce fried rice. Best in DC customer service outstanding steak and cheese fish cheese always fresh and plentiful. Chinese food always on point dive 1984 they have been part of community and they show love

I visited this location on 9/10/21 and had the jerk chicken, mac & cheese, cabbage, and seafood egg rolls. I didn’t care for the seafood egg rolls. They had a strange flavor, but everything else was good. I decided to go back the next day and get the crab fried rice. It didn’t have much crab, which is fine since I wasn’t expecting much for $10. Unfortunately, the rice was bland and scorched. Furthermore, the cashier wasn’t  attentive. I was standing at the register for several minutes and she didn’t acknowledge me. I finally asked if someone was going to take my order. That’s when a man, I’m assuming the owner, directed the cashier to take my order. He gave me a peach cobbler on the house, which was a soggy glob. It was sitting for way too long. I’m not sure if I’ll try this place again.
A wonderful neighborhood dine-in or takeout spot.  The service atmosphere is family and friendly and the food is hot and delicious.  You won't be disappointed.

Went to fusion grill today for breakfast. I love the set up of the restaurant and it’s a nice environment to sit down and eat. The best thing we has was the fish and grits. The fish was seasoned and fried perfectly and the grits were unique in flavor and had a great texture. Only thing is that the wait was very long so I would definitely call ahead in the future. I will be back to try more things.

This is the place to eat at in Deanwood. And then the food is very delicious. Where should I begin their hamburgers are very juicy and delicious. The hot mumbo sauce is great on your french fries and chicken.

5 stars for SURE and Here's why.....

My first Experience was everything!!!! There's nothing like a Professional Black Owned Business, with Excellent Customer Service and Delicious Food. I Love this place already🤗 My sister China and I came here for Dinner on a Saturday night. We left with more than 2 Dinners because it was definitely worth it. But While visiting we met the Owner Kevin, His Chef along with Jessica. They greeted us before Jessica took care of our orders. Please try their Mixed Lemonade and Cornbread. PS: Keep in mind that Fusion Grill is closed on Sundays. Enjoy & Continue to Support DC Restaurants!!!🔥

I wasn't sure they sold Breakfast at first until another store owner told me. I was told that would be fixed soon.

My breakfast was so good and the food reminded me of so many nights eating at the Waffle House down in Atlanta, but better without the local colour. The prices are very reasonable and they have a great selection. Not too many items and something for everyone. I didn't even think to take a pretty food picture as I just dived in.

So bomb. 💖🥰💖

I would definitely recommend this little diner. The staff were very friendly and helpful. The diner was clean and bright. The music was a bit loud for me personally but I have sensory issues so it shouldn't bother anyone else. If you are on the spectrum, definitely bring your Noise Canceling headphones and it will be worth dining here. I will definitely stop back in myself when I'm able.

Thanks for a great experience! 💖🙏🏾
When I tell you the food is all that and then some. I almost for got to take a picture of it. Also Excellent Customer Service as well as Price. Yessssss

OMG!! I really enjoyed the food and dessert. I ordered the dinner platter that came with 1 meat and 2 sides. The ribs came off the grill and tasted so good!! The mac 'n Cheese and yams were ok. For dessert I order strawberry crumb cake!! My God! I enjoyed this resturant. Professional staff, reasonable prices, delicious food and Black Owed!!

My 1st time trying the Soul food.
It was Phenomenal. I purchased 3 plates.
Ribs were so tender,baked Chicken was moist,
Baked fish was also moist.I have an elderly Father,and you know how Elderly people are with their taste buds. They will let you know how their food taste. He bragged on how the Fish was tasty,and The Collard greens,sweet potato's was Delicious.

Well I will  return again
I thoroughly enjoyed my dinners.
The Staff was Very professional, had a pleasant attitude as well. Not like some places.

May God Continue to Bless You with the Strength to go on and serve the Different Communities.

Please forgive me this is so  long
Thank You

I ordered here as a few of my friends recommended them. So I tried to support and ordered the rib and chicken meal.NEVER AGAIN.

ONE, the Mac and cheese with literally just that noodles and cheese. And very greasy. The chicken was fried but soggy on the meat side. Mind you, you get a leg quarter which isn't specified when you order. The ribs were ok but they gave you very little bbq sauce on the side. I livr in the neighborhood.  Please do better.

I find it insulting to go in a black owned establishment to purchase a traditional dish of black people (macaroni and cheese) and receive something as bland, disgusting and processed as this mac and cheese was. Why would you even sell this to people? It's barely edible. There's ZERO cheese in it! U will continue to support black business. Just not this one

Let me start off by saying I love supporting our people but they be the ones with the nasty attitudes all the time my first time visiting this cafe I was excited because it’s always crowded, so I figured the food must be good I order home fries, and a chicken patty. The chicken patty was amazing the home fries taste like burnt plastic the guy or old man that was in the front. He has the worst attitude he should not be on the register. His attitude is very mean and grumpy and it makes you don’t want to go there because how he talks to people. So I gave it another try and the same thing happened he is a very mean guy and don’t know how to speak to people

This food place is located at the bottom of DOES building in DC. The food here is a miss or hit. They don't season their food well which is very surprising being as though they are true Jamaicans. Honestly, the food is not the worst part here it is the customer service. The older gentleman is very rude and obnoxious. I can understand to some degree why he may act the way he does because of  which the environment the business is located in, but that still does not take away having good customer service skills. They do not allow you to even drink outside water/ drinks from other places in this place and don't even think about sitting down for a few minutes without ordering something because they will scold you so much so that it makes you want to leave and not anything. Honestly, save your money and spend it where it is appreciated at.  :)

Jerk chicken sandwich was very dry tasted like no jerk sauce was added in the process and when I asked for jerk sauce on the side she said it was none! So I’m curious what are you cooking with then. I will never waste a dollar in here again!

I’ve been debating if I should even say anything about this because it had nothing to do with me but it’s been bothering me.

The other day I was at Electric Cafe on Minnesota Ave in DC. I’ve been there like 3  times.

I know that nowadays establishments are not open to letting people use their restrooms considering the times we live in. But I saw a woman get extremely disrespected and treated in a way I don’t believe anyone should be.

I’m going to assume she asked to use the bathroom because she was unwell. She appeared to be a Latina ,middle aged, dressed like she was heading to work maybe. A male worker told her no and asked her to leave, then he proceeded to get in her face and yelled at her in front of all the customers.

This woman appeared to really be unwell and was solely trying to gather herself. I was horrified that someone can treat another person that way. I just thought that could be my gma, mom, aunt, friend in that situation and I would want someone to speak up.

I will never return to this establishment and I will make sure to let everyone know this place disrespects ppl in need of help!!
